European stock markets pushed higher at the opening bell on Monday, following gains in Asian markets after China unveiled fresh stimulus measures. In London, the blue-chip FTSE 100 rose 0.5% to 7 315.18 points about a half hour into trading, while the DAX 30 in Frankfurt was 0.3% higher at 12 221.91 and the CAC 40 in Paris added 0.2% to 5 604.18. 